CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 29, 1963, p. 15, reads: "1963 Courier-WAMO Home-A-Rama Exhibitors who were not shown on last week's picture page are shown here...10. North Side Packing Co. (Victory Meats): Mrs. Glennie Anderson, attendant, with James Maulls and William (Bill) Eicher, representatives... All Home-A-Rama photos (including last week's) by Charles (Teenie) Harris."
TitMainTitle: Glennie Anderson handing hot dog to boy, James Maulls, and William Eicher in Victory Meats booth, at 1963 Pittsburgh Courier - WAMO, Home-A-Rama fair, Syria Mosque
